  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Adversarial sample INT-5: W-EP-01 (Critical) triggered by an unsupported claim lacking prov:wasDerivedFrom, and W-AL-02 (Medium) triggered by UQ declared true with no sensitivity analysis present. COMPOUND-01 does not fire because the combination is Critical+Medium, not Critical+High.",
